if we don't want to use IDE, we can use codesandbox.io, It is cloud base IDE.

-----------------------------------------------------
we should use Vite, it is basic boiler-Plate code for react.
https://vitejs.dev/guide/

npm create vite@latest
npm install
npm run dev
----------------------------------
   <!doctype html>
   <html lang="en">
     <head>
       <meta charset="UTF-8" />
       <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/vite.svg" />
       <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
       <title>Vite + React</title>
     </head>
     <body>
       <div id="root">
         <!-- React code will mount Dom over hetre. -->
       </div>
       <script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
       <!-- Her it is also Loading relative files. -->
     </body>
   </html>
-------------------------------------
Shortform keys:-
rfc = react function component
rcc = react class component
rce = reactClassExportComponent
rconst = concept of state
rpce = reactClassPrueExportComponent
